HEADWORD: Stipule
<hw>Stip"ule</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>stipula</ets> a stalk, stem, straw: cf. F. <ets>stipule</ets>. Cf.
<er>Stubble</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>An appendage at the base
of petioles or leaves, usually somewhat resembling a small leaf in
texture and appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stipuled</ent>⟦br⟧
